  "text": "Dialog based ITSs have the same main goal as traditional ITSs, which is to increase the level of engagement and learning gains. However, dialog based ITSs can use different dimensions of evaluation in classifying learner's responses, comprehending learner's contributions, modeling knowledge, and generating conversationally smooth tutorial dialogs. D'Mello and Graesser [CITATION_1] conducted a study to describe how dialog based ITSs can be evaluated along these dimensions using AutoTutor as a case study.",
